### Root Cause: Empty Portal Cache S3 Bucket

Monitor log (`deadlinemonitor-ATXRTX-2026-05-30-0009.log`) shows:
```
Using a custom ReverseDash.template from https://aws-portal-cache-5e77a4fe-5e27-4ea9-83e8-8c330a2bc590.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Release/ReverseDash.template
System.Net.WebException: The remote server returned an error: (403) Forbidden.
```

Investigation:
- Bucket `aws-portal-cache-5e77a4fe-5e27-4ea9-83e8-8c330a2bc590` EXISTS in us-west-2
- Bucket is EMPTY — zero objects (confirmed via `s3api list-objects-v2`)
- `s3api get-object` returns `NoSuchKey` (not AccessDenied)
- Three template files missing:
  - `Release/ReverseDash.template` — main Portal VPC/Gateway CFN template
  - `Release/PrivateSubnet.template` — per-AZ subnet template
  - `Release/amis.json` — AMI mapping file
- No template files found anywhere on disk (searched Program Files, ProgramData, AppData)
- Templates are embedded in the Deadline Monitor .NET assembly and should be uploaded during "Configure AWS Portal"

### Fix Options

1. **Re-run Configure AWS Portal** in Deadline Monitor (Tools → Configure AWS Portal) — re-enter AWS credentials; this should re-extract and upload the templates to the cache bucket
2. **Manual template extraction** from the Deadline assembly and upload to `s3://aws-portal-cache-5e77a4fe-5e27-4ea9-83e8-8c330a2bc590/Release/`
3. After templates are in the bucket, "Start Infrastructure" should work

